{"title":"「2019 山东一轮集训 Day3」小孩召开法","time_limit":1000,"memory_limit":512,"tags":["组合计数","生成函数"],"operation":{"submit":"https://loj.ac/problem/6731#submit_code","submissions":"https://loj.ac/submissions?problem_id=6731","statistics":"https://loj.ac/problem/6731/statistics/fastest","testdata":"https://loj.ac/problem/6731/testdata","discussion":"https://loj.ac/discussion/problem/6731"},"statement":[{"title":"题目描述","type":"description","format":"markdown","require":["katex"],"content":"```plain\r\n小孩召开法，\r\n\r\n旦写一北砬。\r\n\r\n梦厷停留在，\r\n\r\n破了大式様。\r\n\r\n——龚诗锋《炄勺，砒》\r\n```\r\n\r\n小弟递给神树大人一本《阿 Q 外教你学计数》，神树大人看了看第一题，发现不会；神树大人看了看第二题，发现题都读不懂；......；神树大人看了看第 $114514$ 题，终于用 $1919810$ 秒把它做了出来。他决定把这个题写进《神树大人教你做数学》。\r\n\r\n对于长为 $n$ 的一个排列 $\\{a_i\\}$ 的一个子序列 $a_{i_1},a_{i_2},\\dots a_{i_k}$，如果这个子序列满足 $a_{i_1}>a_{i_2}<a_{i_3}\\dots >a_{i_k}$，那么这个子序列被称作**交替子序列**。你要求的就是最长的交替子序列等于 $K$ 的长为 $n$ 的排列有多少个，对 $998244353$ 取模。\r\n"},{"title":"输入格式","type":"input_format","format":"markdown","require":["katex"],"content":"输入 $n,K$。"},{"title":"输出格式","type":"output_format","format":"markdown","require":["katex"],"content":"输出一行答案。\r\n"},{"title":"样例","type":"example","format":"markdown","require":["katex"],"content":"#### 输入样例1\r\n\r\n```plain\r\n3 2\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### 输出样例1\r\n\r\n```plain\r\n3\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### 样例解释\r\n\r\n序列 $[1, 3, 2], [2, 3, 1], [3, 2, 1]$ 符合要求。\r\n\r\n#### 输入样例2\r\n\r\n```plain\r\n10 6\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### 输出样例2\r\n\r\n```plain\r\n878856\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### 输入样例3\r\n\r\n```plain\r\n5000 1145\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### 输出样例3\r\n\r\n```plain\r\n849619090\r\n```"},{"title":"数据范围与提示","type":"limit_and_hint","format":"markdown","require":["katex"],"content":"提示：龚诗锋，小万邦，小弟是一个人。\r\n\r\n另注：千万不要在这道题上浪费太多时间。\r\n\r\n| 子任务 | 分数 | $n$            | $K$                 |\r\n| :------: | :----: | :--------------: | :-------------------: |\r\n| $1$      | $10$   | $\\leq 10$      | $\\leq n$            |\r\n| $2$      | $20$   | $\\leq 5000$    | $\\leq n$            |\r\n| $3$      | $5$    | $\\leq 10^5$    | $=n$                |\r\n| $4$      | $10$   | $\\leq 10^5$    | $\\leq n$            |\r\n| $5$      | $15$   | $\\leq 10^9$    | $\\leq \\min(20,n)$   |\r\n| $6$      | $5$    | $\\leq 10^9$    | $\\leq \\min(200,n)$  |\r\n| $7$     | $35$   | $\\leq 10^{18}$ | $\\leq \\min(10^6,n)$ |"}]}